videoTitle: Is Airbnb Stock a No-Brainer Buy?
comment_text: Its valuation very much depends on macro, I can't say this is an opportunity.  Likely they will grow EPS about 4-5% in 2025, the next years EPS growth is the key. If we bet on depressed discretionary spending (such as tourism expense) and EPS growth over medium term remains between 4-6% per year, then likely fair value over the next 5years is around 70 (plus some brand value premium, moat). At the current price, looks like the market is assuming a much higher EPS growth possibly 5years CAGR of 14%, so if this fails a downside scenario could happen. I wonder if EXPE is not a better bet.
